The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks and deep learning for developing brain co-processors, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques to achieve desired behaviors, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the technology in rehabilitation and augmentation of brain function, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV).
